definition: to cover/to wrap/to hold/to include/to take charge of/to contract (to or for)/package/wrapper/container/bag/to hold or embrace/bundle/packet/CL:個|个[ge4],隻|只[zhi1]

sentences.english: PE Packer is used for paper box, paper case, color printing corporation, etc.

sentences.english: The failure rate is reduced and efficiency is increased in the renovated bundling machine.

sentences.english: Daily charter flights will be fully implemented in the next ten days.

sentences.english: They bought a special machine for baling.
sentences.chinese: 他們買了個專門的打包機。

sentences.english: Its charter business, operated largely by its Lauda Air subsidiary, also could be cut by half.
sentences.chinese: 其子公司勞達航空的包機業務，也可能被縮減一半。

sentences.english: The hot toast popped up in the toaster.

sentences.english: But this time why hasn't it dispatched any chartered plane to evacuate the overseas Chinese from Lebanon?

sentences.english: Mr Zhan left Okinawa on Friday evening on a specially chartered plane sent by the government of China.
sentences.chinese: 詹其雄先生於週五晚上由中國政府包機從沖繩島返回。

sentences.english: Why do you think blenders and toaster ovens are so notoriously unromantic?

sentences.chinese: 如果您訂購一臺烤麪包機，一家公司將其寄送給你。

sentences.english: The player with Bread and Toaster on the table wins.
sentences.chinese: 在桌面上放有面包和烤麪包機的玩家獲勝。

sentences.english: An ordinary toaster has more than 400 components and sub-components.
sentences.chinese: 一臺普通烤麪包機有400多個零件和子零件。

sentences.english: In this paper, the control systems of chemical fiber baler are used as a example.
sentences.chinese: 在這篇文章中以化纖打包機的控制系統爲例。

sentences.english: I informed the toaster, which was now in control of my body, that I wished it to fetch help.
sentences.chinese: 我對正控制着我身體的麪包機說，我想獲得幫助。

sentences.english: This travel frm specializes in charter flights.
